svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ttw1665702607229.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ttw1665702607229.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ttw1665702607229.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ttw1665702607229\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__blockdata_210555\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Defines a constant block of text.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__topic_d69803e1_d69804e1_d69805e1\">\n<div class=\"zDocsCodeExplanationContainer\"><button aria-label=\"Explain this code\" class=\"zDocsAiActionsButton\" data-target=\"#zDocsCodeExplanationModal_uniface_104ttw1665702607229_html_0\" data-toggle=\"modal\" tabindex=\"0\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-code-explanation\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-code-explanation\"></use></svg>Explain this code</button></div><div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" data-explanation-rendered=\"true\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__codeblock_z3d_k5z_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\"><var class=\"keyword varname\">BlockName:</var>blockdata  <var class=\"keyword varname\">Delimiter</var>\n...\n... <var class=\"keyword varname\">text</var> ...\n...\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Delimiter</var></code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section p\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__section_w1367ab1b7b5_w1368ab1b7_w1369ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__p_d69809e1_d69810e1_d69811e1\">Example: <code class=\"ph codeph\">TextA:blockdata +</code></p>\n<p class=\"p\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">This is a block of text that can be assigned to a field or variable +</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__topic_d45742e1_d45743e1_d45744e1_d45745e1_d45746e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d197231e86\">\n                       \n Parameters\n </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Parameters</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__1\">\n Parameter\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__2\">\n Data Type\n </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__3\">\n Description\n </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">BlockName</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__3\">\n Name of block; maximum of 8 characters.\n </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Delimiter</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__3\">Beginning and end of the text block. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">text</var>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__2\">\n String\n </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"ttw1665702607229__table_d6119e1_d6120e1_d6121e1__entry__3\">\n All lines are considered part of the text until the character <var class=\"keyword varname\">Delimiter</var> is encountered.\n </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__topic_d45747e1_d45748e1_d45749e1_d45750e1_d45751e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d197231e173\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__d5966e20\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__topic_d45752e1_d45753e1_d45754e1_d45755e1_d45756e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d197231e183\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__topic_d45757e1_d45758e1_d45759e1_d45760e1_d45761e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d197231e192\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__p_d69830e1_d69831e1_d69832e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span> statement is often used to define long <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">sql</span> statements.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__p_d69833e1_d69834e1_d69835e1\">The following rules apply to the use of <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span>:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__li_d31766e1_d31767e1_d31768e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span> statement must\n               be in the same ProcScript module as the statement that references the\n                  <var class=\"keyword varname\">BlockName</var>. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__li_d31769e1_d31770e1_d31771e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span> statement must be at the end of the ProcScript module.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__li_d31772e1_d31773e1_d31774e1\">More than one <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span> statement is allowed in the ProcScript module.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__li_d31775e1_d31776e1_d31777e1\">In a ProcScript statement (for example, assignment or <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">putmess</span>), refer to <var class=\"keyword varname\">BlockName</var> as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">BlockName</var>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__li_d31778e1_d31779e1_d31780e1\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">BlockName</var> cannot exceed eight characters in length.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__li_d31781e1_d31782e1_d31783e1\">The hash character (#) is not allowed as <var class=\"keyword varname\">Delimiter</var>.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__li_d31784e1_d31785e1_d31786e1\">Substituting variables (using two percent signs (<code class=\"ph codeph\">%%</code>)) is not possible within <var class=\"keyword varname\">text</var>, although you can use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$string</span> to address this. For example:\n <div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">vBlock = $my_block ; does not substitute variables\nvBlockFinal = $string(vBlock) ; variables substituted </code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__p_d69836e1_d69837e1_d69838e1\">However, if the <var class=\"keyword varname\">text</var> contains compile-time constants such as <code class=\"ph codeph\">&lt;this_app_version&gt;</code>, these are not resolved.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__section_zlx_wt1_wbc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d197231e290\">Example: Using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span></h2>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example shows the use of the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span>\n            statement to define the text of a letter:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__pre_g5w_xt1_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">; trigger: Detail\nTEXT = $reject\nmessage \"Standard refusal loaded in TEXT field.\"\nreject:blockdata +\nWe regret to inform you that your qualifications do not match our current\nvacancy and that we have hired somebody else. Your application\nhas been filed for future reference. Thank you for considering us.\nYours sincerely,+\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\">The following example shows how to use <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">blockdata</span> in\n            operations. The <var class=\"keyword varname\">BlockData</var> definition must be in the same ProcScript\n            module in which it is referenced.</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"ttw1665702607229__pre_kjh_xt1_wbc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">operation GET_TEXT1\n message/info $Text1\nText1:blockdata +\nThis is Text One+\n;\nend\noperation GET_TEXT2\n message/info $Text2\n;\nText2:blockdata +\nThis is text Two+\n;\nend\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gtm1665702624482.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Script Modules</a><p>A script module is a named collection of ProcScript belonging to a development object. Script modules are analogous to events and methods in other programming languages.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616193\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616193\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "blockdata Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Defines a constant block of text. Explain this code BlockName: blockdata Delimiter ... ... text ... ... Delimiter Copy Example: TextA:blockdata + This is a block of text that can be assigned to a field or variable + Parameters Table 1. Parameters Parameter Data Type Description BlockName String Name of block; maximum of 8 characters. Delimiter String Beginning and end of the text block. text String All lines are considered part of the text until the character Delimiter is encountered. Return Values None Use Allowed in all component types. Description The blockdata statement is often used to define long sql statements. The following rules apply to the use of blockdata : The blockdata statement must be in the same ProcScript module as the statement that references the BlockName . The blockdata statement must be at the end of the ProcScript module. More than one blockdata statement is allowed in the ProcScript module. In a ProcScript statement (for example, assignment or putmess ), refer to BlockName as $ BlockName . BlockName cannot exceed eight characters in length. The hash character (#) is not allowed as Delimiter . Substituting variables (using two percent signs ( %% )) is not possible within text , although you can use $string to address this. For example: vBlock = $my_block ; does not substitute variables vBlockFinal = $string(vBlock) ; variables substituted Copy However, if the text contains compile-time constants such as <this_app_version> , these are not resolved. Example: Using blockdata The following example shows the use of the blockdata statement to define the text of a letter: ; trigger: Detail TEXT = $reject message \"Standard refusal loaded in TEXT field.\" reject:blockdata + We regret to inform you that your qualifications do not match our current vacancy and that we have hired somebody else. Your application has been filed for future reference. Thank you for considering us. Yours sincerely,+ Copy The following example shows how to use blockdata in operations. The BlockData definition must be in the same ProcScript module in which it is referenced. operation GET_TEXT1 message/info $Text1 Text1:blockdata + This is Text One+ ; end operation GET_TEXT2 message/info $Text2 ; Text2:blockdata + This is text Two+ ; end Copy Related Links Script Modules A script module is a named collection of ProcScript belonging to a development object. Script modules are analogous to events and methods in other programming languages. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}